Make instanceOf and throwError be aliased like others

Fix should[.not].exist not having stack trace #84

This was because should wasn't defined in that context and was referring
to should property of the `global` object which is from the prototype.
So `should.exist` and `should.not.exist` were undefined, which made
stackStartFunction properties in those functions undefined.

use valueOf() to get the reference the object.

It seems as though new versions of V8 (as of node v0.7.7) will return an
Object version of a primitive when it is referenced using "this", something
silly like this would fail:

  var called = false
  called.should.equal.false

  AssertionError: expected {} to be false

Merge pull request #55 from gabrielfalcao/master

Proposing a fallback of `.instanceof` as `.instanceOf`

proposing a fallback of .instanceof to .instanceOf
that will give an option for those who want to use `instanceOf` due a jshint running in strict mode.

IMHO it might both do not cause any evil, as well as will make some continuous integration servers very happy
